Display conversion candidates by external conversion engine

This function allows you to perform Japanese conversion using external conversion engine such as a Web dictionary server on the Internet. When you tap the button \"Extra Conv\" in the prediction/conversion candidate area, inputting characters for conversion, including personal data like passwords and credit card numbers, might be sent to the external conversion engine through the Internet. Use this function?

string.name: ti_tip_to_step1_txt
string.b: "Like a normal mobile keyboard, tapping ○ three times will result in *C*."

string.name: ti_tip_to_step2_a_txt
string.b: "For example, let's type \"hi.\" - Tap ○ twice to get \"h\""

string.name: ti_tip_to_step2_b_txt
string.b: " - Tap → to advance to the right"

string.name: ti_tip_to_step2_d_txt
string.b: " - Use touch or ↓ to set the word."

string.name: ti_tip_to_step3_a_txt
string.b: The ■ key switches between Japanese, English, and number input.

string.name: ti_tip_to_step3_b_txt
string.b: "We've switched from English to numbers. Next is Japanese."

string.name: ti_tip_to_step4_txt
string.b: "For other input modes (like full width) or a PC style keyboard, hold ■ for 3 seconds to show the input menu."

string.name: ti_tip_to_step5_txt
string.b: "When you're done typing, hit the \"back\" key (←) to close the keyboard."

string.name: ti_tip_to_step6_txt
string.b: This is the end of the tutorial.
